description: There's a reason why the Jeep CJ5 was the longest production run of CJ's since the 40's. With a slightly widened and stretched stance over the earlier models, the 1975 CJ5 quickly became more desireable. And when in 1972, AMC's 304 cu in (5.0 L) V8 engine became available which upgraded the power to weight ratio making the vehicle somewhat of an V8 muscle car. This one in particular has a fiberglass tub to help cut down on the weight and assist in being more agile. Topped off with a nice upgraded rollbar. All of that goes perfectly with the full floating Dana 30 axle, and a manual 3 spd transmission. Come see it in person!
